<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-23T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 793.94/308.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-23T19:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1915—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At the conference of April 19 no progress was made as the Japanese
                            withheld agreement on Manchuria and the Chinese refused to commit
                            themselves on Group V or make further concessions respecting the
                            Hanyehping Company.</p>
                        <p>As the negotiations had thus come to a deadlock it was necessary for the
                            Japanese Government to decide whether to accept the liberal concessions
                            made by China or to attempt to create a new basis of action. As both of
                            the conferences were prorogued at the request of Japan it is evident
                            that an important decision is impending based upon the situation here
                            and taking into account the attitude of the Powers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
